Next, we want to count the number of words in a sentence.

text = "Welcome to HKU!"
word_count = sapply(strsplit(text, " "), length)
print(word_count)
## [1] 3

Counting sentence is a bit more complex. You need to define what a sentence is.

text <- 'Hello world!! Here are two sentences for you...'
length(gregexpr('[[:alnum:] ][.!?]', text)[[1]])
## [1] 2

##  [219] "of paying a high price in order to avoid advertisements, and when they would not offer consumers"                                                                                                                    
##  [220] "such an option. Research shows that consumers who"                                                                                                                                                                   
##  [221] "switch between channels are less valuable than exclusive"                                                                                                                                                            
##  [222] "consumers (Athey et al. 2014, Ambrus et al. 2017)."                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [223] "As the proportion of such multihoming consumers"                                                                                                                                                                     
##  [224] "increases, each platform increases the advertising"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [225] "level and earns less profits. This body of literature"                                                                                                                                                               
##  [226] "focuses on the consumer side and the advertiser side"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [227] "of the media market but abstracts away from the"                                                                                                                                                                     
##  [228] "content side of the market. The platform in our model"                                                                                                                                                               
##  [229] "connects three sides of the media market: consumers,"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [230] "advertisers, and content suppliers. Moreover, unlike"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [231] "most existing studies that only capture consumersâ\200\231"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [232] "dislike for advertisements and advertisersâ\200\231 desire for"                                                                                                                                                            
##  [233] "consumers, our framework captures consumersâ\200\231 desire for content. Furthermore, we examine how a"                                                                                                                    
##  [234] "platform should allocate its limited bandwidth for"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [235] "content and advertising."                                                                                                                                                                                            
##  [236] "Our work also adds to the literature on content"                                                                                                                                                                     
##  [237] "provision by media firms (for a review, see Peitz and"                                                                                                                                                               
##  [238] "Reisinger 2015). In an early work, Prasad et al. (2003)"                                                                                                                                                             
##  [239] "examine a monopoly platform that offers its own"                                                                                                                                                                     
##  [240] "content. The consumer market comprises two segments, with one segment valuing the content more"                                                                                                                      
##  [241] "than the other, whereas the advertiser market includes firms with heterogeneous margins. Using this"                                                                                                                 
##  [242] "setting, they identify conditions when it is profitable"                                                                                                                                                             
##  [243] "for the monopoly platform to discriminate between"                                                                                                                                                                   
##  [244] "the two segments of consumers by offering them two"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [245] "options: a higher price with fewer ads and a lower"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [246] "price with more ads. In contrast to Prasad et al. (2003),"                                                                                                                                                           
##  [247] "we allow for interplatform competition, let the platform procure its content from independent content"                                                                                                               
##  [248] "suppliers, and vary the level of competition in the"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [249] "content market. The addition of a third side to the"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [250] "market helps us to delineate the effects of consumersâ\200\231"                                                                                                                                                            
##  [251] "desire for content and advertisersâ\200\231 desire for consumers on the content supplierâ\200\231s profits, and also investigate how a platformâ\200\231s content provision strategy"                                                  
##  [252] "varies with the structure of the content market. Gal-Or"                                                                                                                                                             
##  [253] "and Dukes (2003) show that competing platforms"                                                                                                                                                                      
##  [254] "might offer minimally differentiated content. This"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [255] "reduces the intensity of advertising and thereby the"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [256] "competition among advertisers in the product market, which helps the platforms to charge more for"                                                                                                                   
##  [257] "advertising. Upon empirically examining the content"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [258] "quality of 3,000 bloggers in China, Sun and Zhu (2013)"                                                                                                                                                              
##  [259] "report that bloggers, who partake in the advertising"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [260] "revenue of the platform, write about popular topics"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [261] "such as the stock market and celebrity news. Yao"                                                                                                                                                                    
##  [262] "et al. (2016) find that within-show TV commercials"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [263] "create a better viewing experience for highly rated"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [264] "content but not for poorly rated content. Next, we"

##  [471] "4.2. Platformsâ\200\231 Strategies and Profits"                                                                                                                                                                            
##  [472] "Here we first discuss a platformâ\200\231s choice of strategy,"                                                                                                                                                            
##  [473] "and then examine how the choice is influenced by"                                                                                                                                                                    
##  [474] "market characteristics. In principle, a platform could"                                                                                                                                                              
##  [475] "adopt one of the three potential content provision"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [476] "strategies: a free-content strategy, a paid-contentwith-ads strategy, or a no-ad strategy. However,"                                                                                                                 
##  [477] "neither of the competing platforms adopts a no-ad"                                                                                                                                                                   
##  [478] "strategy (see Equation (10)). To understand why, note"                                                                                                                                                               
##  [479] "that in the current formulation, advertising neither"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [480] "annoys consumers nor directly induces a disutility."                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [481] "As a result, a platform always allocates a proportion"                                                                                                                                                               
##  [482] "of its space for advertising and earns profits from advertisers without any backlash from consumers. One"                                                                                                            
##  [483] "could argue that consumers regard advertising as a"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [484] "nuisance and thus dislike advertising. We explore the"                                                                                                                                                               
##  [485] "strategic implications of this possibility in Section 7."                                                                                                                                                            
##  [486] "Given that a platform is not motivated to adopt a"                                                                                                                                                                   
##  [487] "no-ad strategy, it could adopt either a free-content"                                                                                                                                                                
##  [488] "strategy or a paid-content-with-ads strategy. From"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [489] "Equation (10), we know that platforms adopt a freecontent strategy if the suppliersâ\200\231 marginal cost of"                                                                                                             
##  [490] "producing content is large but pursue a paid-contentwith-ads strategy otherwise. To appreciate this result,"                                                                                                         
##  [491] "recall that in a perfectly competitive market, content"                                                                                                                                                              
##  [492] "suppliers sell content at the marginal cost. As the"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [493] "marginal cost increases, it becomes costlier for a"                                                                                                                                                                  
##  [494] "platform to attract consumers by offering them more"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [495] "content. Hence, a platform allocates a lower proportion of its space for content, and comes to rely"                                                                                                                 
##  [496] "more on profits from advertisers. When the marginal"                                                                                                                                                                 
##  [497] "cost is sufficiently high, a platform allocates only a"                                                                                                                                                              
##  [498] "limited space for content and generates all its profits"                                                                                                                                                             
##  [499] "from advertising. Thus, when the marginal cost of"                                                                                                                                                                   
##  [500] "content increases beyond a certain threshold, platforms transition from pursuing a paid-content-withads strategy to adopting a free-content strategy."                                                               
##  [501] "Having understood platformsâ\200\231 equilibrium strategy choice, we turn to examining how the choice is"                                                                                                                  
##  [502] "shaped by market characteristics. We have the following finding."
